Job Details:
At Kartu Prakerja, the Software Engineer role is at very critical to run the business process of the company. We are looking for a Senior Software Engineer Backend passionate about build a reliable workflow system that runs smoothly despite of heavy user traffic! You will join a dynamic and fast-paced environment and work with cross-functional teams to design, build and roll out the product that delivers the organisation’s vision and strategy.
Job Descriptions
Develop a reliable and scalable engineering system and API;
Develop code and library that easy to maintain and follow clean code best practices;
Optimise code and application to run with efficient computing resource and maximise the throughput;
Ensure performance of system through defensive coding with proper logging, monitoring, and alerting;
Implement security and data protection practice within the system domain.
Identify and improve bottlenecks or bugs in the system domain.
Collaborate with other engineer colleagues like Software Engineer Frontend, DevOps Engineer, Product Manager, Data Engineer, Data Analyst;
Requirements
Proficient in Ruby on rails or Golang
Have experience developing microservice with GRPC protocol,
Have experience with virtualization technology like VM, Docker, Kubernetes;
Understand of framework like ReactJS, Typescript, Node JS
Have experience using Cloud Technology like GCP, Aliyun (Alibaba Cloud),
Understand DDD (Domain Design Driven) and Event driven concept,
Have experience using event-driven system like Kafka, NSQ, Rabbit MQ, etc,
Have experience with Database like RDS Postgresql, Mysql, Redis, ElasticSearch for day-to-day operation,
Understand and can operation CI/CD tools like Gitlab Automation, Jenkins;
Benefits
Working with the biggest Innovation Public Services in Indonesia
Working on the product used by 100 Millions of people in Indonesia from 514 city and district
Working hybrid (WHF and WFO)\

Innovation Engineering SRL, a dynamic and innovative IT company part of PNO Group, specialized in the design, development, and maintenance of advanced IT solutions is looking for a Java Backend Developer to join our team.
What are we looking for:
An experienced Java Backend Developer with a focus on innovation and development and a commitment to excellence. You’ve had a similar position for the last 3 years or more, most likely in another IT Company or a technology partner. Ability to plan and organize work and problem solving, result orientation, proactivity, good interpersonal skills, and aptitude for teamwork.
Requirements
Knowledge of Java language, NoSQL (e.g. MongoDB and ElasticSearch), Java frameworks (Spring Boot, Spring Security, JPA, Hibernate, JUnit, Spring Batch);
Knowledge of at least one broker (e.g. RabbitMQ, Kafka);
Manage deadlines and push the team to ensure timeliness;
Knowledge of development and versioning environments (e.g. Eclipse, GIT);
Basic knowledge of SQL language;
Knowledge of: Docker, Kubernetes, Jenkins, Sonarqube, Ubuntu, Apache Solr, Azure, AWS, Google Cloud is an advantage;
Minimum of 3 years of proven experience in a related field;
Excellent verbal and written communication skills, both in English and Italian;
Ability to collaborate with internal and external teams;
Experience in managing a team;
Strong analytical and problem-solving skills;
Excellent communication skills;
Ability to work in a fast-paced environment and be deadline driven.
Why you should join Innovation Engineering:
Participation in national and international innovative and research projects, in an international and rapidly growing organization.
Opportunity to differentiate one's skills and develop one's professionalism in a stimulating and highly educational context.
Opportunity to be part of a dynamic and energetic group made up of great professionals and with concrete growth possibilities.
Permanent contract: salary and classification will be commensurate with previous experience.
Internal training and provided through training companies selected based on needs and the company growth plan.
A policy that supports smart-working up to 100% of one's time if necessary and promotes work-life balance.
